[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Minecraft has sold over 300 million copies", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image from Minecraft Live 2023 featuring three Minecraft characters standing in a field of flowers looking up at the sky.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2Rjt5MkaB_uszOqt-5Jk7TTA5mo=/266x0:3191x1950/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72758190/MCL23_HeroImage2_NOLOGO.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Mojang</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LUxshG\"><em>Minecraft</em> already has the distinction of being <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/5/18/21262045/minecraft-sales-monthly-players-statistics-youtube\">the bestselling video game of all time</a>. Today, it adds more down to that particular feather in its cap with the announcement that it has sold a staggering 300 million copies. </p>\n<p id=\"ZEou6l\">\u201cAs we approach the 15th anniversary, <em>Minecraft</em> remains one of the best-selling games of all time, with over 300 million copies sold, a milestone no one could have dreamed of when we were all placing our first blocks,\u201d Helen ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/15/23916349/minecraft-mojang-sold-300-million-copies-live-2023", "date_published": "2023-10-15T18:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Apple rumors claim refreshed iPads are coming this week", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image of the Apple logo surrounded by gray, pink, and green outlines\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-TEhN5cIiZZCwxOPT0Fmj7YSrZI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72758109/VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_5_apple.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zqyama\">Apple may have a surprise iPad u